at least 4 years of administrative experience preferably in drafting administration policy/staff welfare schemes or project management;
proficiency in English and Chinese, and preferably in Putonghua;
calibre as a good team player with supervisory experience and sound communication skills; and
ability to work independently with initiative and have a strong sense of responsibility.

(Please specify in the application form the HKCEE result and relevant working experience you have attained in detail.)

